nce issues previously discussed in the author's Text and Act (1995)—that appear in print for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMusical criticism. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  a21st century art criticism.  a21st century music criticism.  aaesthetics.  aanti utopian thought.  aart post 9/11.  aarts.  abach.  abeethoven.  aboris goudenow.  acareer.  aclassical music.  acolonialism.  acontemporary composition.  acontemporary performance.  acritics.  aethics.  aezra pound.  ahindemith legacy.  ahistorians.  alifetime.  amodernism.  amusic.  amusicology.  anationalism.  anature.  aoptimism.  aperformance.  apolitical art.  apolitics.  apublic musicologist.  apundits.  asterility.  astravinsky.  aterrorist attacks.  ateutonic train wreck.  athe new york times.  awagner.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094279040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520942790423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520942790/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles